Three people were injured following a shootout at Twist Street in Park Central, Johannesburg on Friday. Netcare911 spokesperson Nick Dollman said reports from the scene alleged that a shootout ensued when a gang attacked armed cash guards. “Netcare911 and other paramedics from the city of Johannesburg attended to the three patients at the scene,” Dollman said. The patients included an armed cash guard, the suspect and a female bystander who was caught in the crossfire. Dollman said the suspect and the cash guard are both in critical conditions but the woman injured is stable. The police also attended the scene for further investigations. -TNA Reporter